# Trivy accepted-risk exceptions for `trivy config`.
# Every entry must have a justification, an owner, and an expiry (exp:YYYY-MM-DD)
# so suppressions are reviewed instead of living forever.

# AZU-0041: API server is publicly reachable with no IP allowlist by default.
# Justification: this baseline ships a public-API cluster suitable for dev/CI,
# where access is gated by Entra ID + Azure RBAC. The Helm provider and
# `az aks get-credentials` also need to reach the API from outside the VNet.
# To remove this exception: set var.api_server_authorized_ip_ranges to your
# egress CIDRs (or enable a private cluster), then delete this line.
# Owner: platform-team
AZU-0041 exp:2026-12-31
